^b{ Showing support for Partners Major after a Take-out Double by RHO }|fp|1|ht|f|cs|3|at|

^b@2Here is the basic situation: You are  in third seat, your partner opened 1@h or 1@s, 
and RHO does something other than pass

Let's start with the simplest thing: your pard opens 1@h (say), and RHO doubles
You have some support, say 3 cards, and some points. Let's say between 6 and 9
You would raise 1@h to 2@h with such a hand without the double, right? 
example: @sxx, @hQxx, @dKJxx, @cJxxx
Just raise to 2 @h 
A single raise of 1@H or 1@S to 2M is exactly the same kind of hand you would raise wihtout the double
That is the easy stuff

Now, let's suppose you have a 4 card raise
If your hand is really weak (0 to 6 points), raise to 3!!
I also insist on some shape (preferably a singleton somewhere), but I will do this with a
doubleton in the other major, too
Example: 1@h (x) and you have @sxxx, @hQxxx, @dx, @cxxxxx 
Bid 3@h. Just do it!
Will you get doubled? Maybe, but the defenders need trump tricks to be comfortable in doubling.
And if they can beat you a lot of tricks, they probably can make game on their own|
